---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Home from "../components/Home.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <Home />

  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <!-- 使用说明 -->
    <section id="how-to" class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
      <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-question"></i>How to use CompareJSON</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-16">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-700 rounded-lg">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
            <div
              class="bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/50 text-green-600 dark:text-green-300 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3"
            >
              <i class="fas fa-keyboard"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>
              What are the methods for inputting data?
            </h4>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>1. Paste the JSON content directly in the text box</li>
            <li>2. Click the upload icon to select a local JSON file</li>
            <li>3. Drag and drop the JSON file to the upload area</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-700 rounded-lg">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-2">
            <div
              class="bg-rose-100 dark:bg-rose-900/50 text-rose-600 dark:text-rose-300 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3"
            >
              <i class="fas fa-file-code"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>
              What do the results of a JSON comparison mean?
            </h4>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <span class="diff-unchanged px-1">Same key value</span> - Data with
              the same key and value in two JSON contents
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="diff-changed px-1">Same key but different value</span
              > - Two JSON contents have the same key but different values
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="diff-added px-1">Only JSON1</span> - Only keys present
              in the first JSON
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="diff-removed px-1">Only JSON2</span> - Only keys present
              in the second JSON
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="terms bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
      <h3><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Terms of Service</h3>

      <h4>1. Service Description</h4>
      <p>
        This JSON comparison tool provides an online JSON data comparison
        service, allowing users to input JSON data for comparative analysis.
      </p>

      <h4>2. User Obligations</h4>
      <p>
        You agree to use this service only for legitimate purposes and not to
        attempt to undermine the security, stability or availability of the
        service.
      </p>

      <h4>3. Data Privacy and Security</h4>
      <p>We value your data security:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>No data upload</strong>: All JSON data comparison processing
          is done in your browser, and your data will never leave your device
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No server storage</strong>: We will not store any JSON data
          you enter on the server
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No data collection</strong>: We will not collect, sell or
          share any of your personal data or JSON content
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="highlight">
        <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Important: Since all data processing is
        done in the local browser, all input data will disappear permanently after
        closing the browser window.
      </div>

      <h4>4. Disclaimer</h4>
      <p>
        This service is provided "as is" without any express or implied
        warranty. We are not responsible for any loss or damage arising from the
        use of this service.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
      <h3><i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i> Privacy Policy</h3>

      <h4>1. Information we collect</h4>
      <p>We are committed to minimizing data collection:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>No personal identification information is collected</strong>:
          We do not need or collect personal information such as your name,
          email, address, etc.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No JSON content is collected</strong>: The JSON data you enter
          for comparison will not leave your browser
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Basic usage data</strong>: We only collect anonymized usage
          statistics to improve the service
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h4>2. Use of cookies</h4>
      <p>We use cookies to enhance your user experience:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Functional cookies</strong>: Save your preferences (such as
          theme selection, layout preferences)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics Cookies</strong>: Collect anonymous usage data to
          understand how users interact with our Services
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Session Cookies</strong>: Maintain your login status (if
          applicable) and session information
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="highlight">
        <i class="fas fa-cookie-bite"></i> You can manage or disable cookies at any
        time through your browser settings, but this may affect certain Service features.
      </div>

      <h4>3. Third-Party Services</h4>
      <p>
        We may use third-party analytics services, such as Google Analytics, to
        collect anonymous usage data. These services use cookies but do not
        collect personally identifiable information.
      </p>

      <h4>4. Policy Changes</h4>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time.
        Significant changes will be notified on the Site.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="data-usage  dark:text-zinc-700">
      <div class="card blue bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
        <i class="fas fa-ban"></i>
        <h4>We do not collect</h4>
        <p>Your JSON data</p>
        <p>Personally identifiable information</p>
        <p>Sensitive personal information</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card green bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
        <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
        <h4>We only use</h4>
        <p>Functional cookies (preferences)</p>
        <p>Analytical cookies (anonymous data)</p>
        <p>Session cookies (logged in)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
